        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:41PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 540 PM MDT, Doppler radar and satellite were tracking a strong
thunderstorm over Garrison, or 8 miles north of Deer Lodge, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, half-inch size hail, localized
heavy rainfall, and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar and satellite indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Ponding on roadways and localized minor flooding
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blossburg, Finn, Elliston, and Avon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 near mile marker 188.
Highway 12 Garrison to MacDonald Pass between mile markers 15 and
21.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
